cs.CV, cs.BIO, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper involves computer vision techniques applied to medical imaging data, specifically surgical video. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves physiological modeling, which suggests a potential fit for cs.BIO (Computational Biology). Additionally, the paper focuses on improving surgical procedures, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) or cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves video processing, which could also fit under cs.MM (Multimedia).
